```csharp
private static bool ProcessPayment(decimal amount)
{
    if (amount == 0) throw new ArgumentException("Amount cannot be zero");
    // Missing: validation for negative amounts
    return true;
}
```

It doesn't throw for negative amounts. So `Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentException>(() => ProcessPayment(-50.00m))` should FAIL because no exception is thrown. But `dotnet test` says all tests pass... That's weird.


